message:
I have like 3 tasks and i wanted to use them in WhenAll()

```cs
var firstTask = Task.Factory.StartNew(() => CallMethod1ReturnsListOfString());
var secondTask = Task.Factory.StartNew(() => CallMethod2ReturnsListofString());
var thirdTask = Task.Factory.StartNew(() => CallMethod3ReturnsIEnumerableOfMyObject());
```

If i use, 
```c#
var finalTask = Task.WhenAll( firstTask, secondTask); //returns a collection of TaskResult
```

It returns a collectiion of Tasks for finalTask and i can use finalTask[0] and finalTask[1] to access the results. I assume, they return a collection because, each task's return type is same. but if i add a task that is of different type, then it just returns Task object from Task.WhenAll()

say,
```c#
var finalTask = Task.WhenAll( firstTask, secondTask, thirdTask); //returns Task as return value;
```

In that situation, how do i access the results of each of these tasks execution? 

In other words, if i have 3 different return data elements as tasks and wanted to use WhenAll(), how do i access their results? Is it implicit to use 

```cs
var firstResult = await firstTask;
var secondResult = await secondTask;
...
var thirdResult = await thirdTask;
```
